14:
Grr, and they're creepy as hell. How
did the guild describe 'em again?
17:
Unidentifiable organisms with
unidentifiable origins, who come out
of the woodwork every night.
19:
They haven't attacked anyone yet,
but we were asked to put them
down as a safety measure.
24:
If they ain't a threat, why not leave
'em be?
26:
Ugh, bore me to death, why don't
you?
29:
Every day's a party, right? Where's
your festive spirit? Hahahaha!
32:
Idiot! Don't show them your face!
Retreat already!
46:
Ahahaha! Chase me down, did you?
That's cool.
55:
Fool girl! Listen for once in your life!
Your body can't handle—
66:
That's what you get for making too
many shadows! Nincompoop!
69:
Well, guess it's curtains for me.
Ahahaha, show's over, Cob!
72:
Sorry, but are you a monster or a
human?
78: Hey, Shrimpy! Let this girl go! Please!
81: Ugh, Cob, begging is SO lame.
84:
Begging is all that stands between
you and swift death!
88:
Please! She was just playing! There's
no need to slay her! Let us go!
91:
Ahah. It's cool. I'd rather die than
beg.
102: Whoa, did you knock that one out?
106: Actually, she did that to herself...
110:
The others aren't far behind. What
do we do?
113:
Hm. Let's get her back to Starview
Village.
119:
Ah! You'll save us? Truly? Really?
Thank you, dearest mortal!
123:
Bwuh? Dude, just kill me. I'm a
monster, after all.
127:
I won't harm someone who can't
defend herself. Can you stand?
131:
Ah, I get it. You're into monster girls.
Gross, dude.
135:
That's not it at all! Hurry! Other
people will be here soon!
145:
Ahahaha! Heck yeah! Just look at
this place!
150:
Gravy on toast, return my platform
at once!
154:
What is she? There's a terrifying
aura to her visage, but more
worrying is her—
158:
Call me Carla. Let's leave it at that,
'kay?
164:
Though I guess I'm not really human
anymore. That's fair enough to say.
167:
Wait... Is your current form the result
of a curse?
170:
Hmm. Don't know if I'd call this a
curse. Now I can run FAST and
punch HARD.
172: All it cost was half my life span!
175:
You mean you traded your soul for
power?!
179:
Yep. It was a fair contract, signed by
both parties.
183:
I explained everything before she
agreed. And there wasn't even any
fine print. That's better than your
mortal contracts, huh?
187:
So what did you wish for in
exchange for half your life?
197:
I was down in that dumb maze
when THIS dumb snake was like,
"Help, I'm dying! I need your life force
to sustain myself!"
200: And I was like, "Sure, whatev's, dude."
206:
You guys have to tell her to think of
a wish. If she doesn't come up with
one, I'll never be able to part with her.
210:
So we should help her find an
ambition?
221:
Are you sure we should encourage
her, Stella?
226:
Hey, aren't you the doofus who
brought me here?
236: Good luck wrangling that one, Alk.
